Intuition
To find the first occurrence of one string (needle) inside another string (haystack), Java already provides a built-in method that efficiently handles this operation. Using it avoids unnecessary manual comparisons and keeps the solution concise.

Approach
We use Java’s String.indexOf() method:

indexOf(needle) returns the index of the first occurrence of needle in haystack.

If needle does not exist in haystack, it automatically returns -1.

This directly satisfies the problem requirements, so we simply return the result.

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)

Space complexity:
O(1)

Code
class Solution {
    public int strStr(String haystack, String needle) {
        int res= haystack.indexOf(needle);
        return res;
    }
}
